The '''Department of Natural Resources and Environmental Control''' (DNREC) of the [[U.S. state|state]] of [[Delaware]] is the primary body concerned with the governance of [[public land]], [[natural resource]]s, and [[Environmental law|environmental regulations]] for the state. DNREC is composed of several Divisions that have correlates in other U.S. State governments: <!-- expand on the roles of each ... redirects point here, tagged with {{tl|R to list entry}} --> * Division of Air and Waste Management * Division of Fish and Wildlife * Division of Parks and Recreation * Division of Soil and Water Conservation * Division of Water Resources The Department is headed by an 'Office of the Secretary'. <!-- elected or appointed? term? political or apolitical -->
==History== In April 2005, the first law enforcement shooting in the history of the Department took place. The incident involved 2 park rangers and resulted in the death of a robbery suspect.<ref>{{cite news |first=Terri |last=Sanginiti |title=Man killed by rangers used gun in earlier crime |publisher=[[The News Journal]] |pages=B1-2 |date=2006-04-26 }}</ref>
